From Henry Spencer Subject Re temperature of the dark sky In article Tom Van Flandern writes temperature of the night sky as seen from space You'll find that in Allen Astrophysical Quantities Athlone Press Dover NH edition I have a copy of Allen and it never occurred to me to look in I must be getting I'll look it up when I get the temperature is degrees I'd remembered a rather higher number but that may have been for the lunar nearside where the Earth is a significant heat resembles a high speed collision Henry Spencer U of Toronto Zoology between and Dick Dunn utzoo henry